news.title: Government land worth Rs 1,500 crore allegedly transferred to private individuals in Sircilla
news.para: The district administration has begun investigating the widespread land scam and identified that 1,300 acres to 1,400 acres of land was illegally grabbed, particularly in seven to eight villages along main roads.

news.title: Ranchi civic body issues warning to holding tax defaulters
news.para: The RMC has published a list of defaulters along with a notice, serving as a final warning for holding owners to comply with their tax obligations and avoid potential disruptions in their businesses.

news.title: Somwarpet delegation discusses C&D land issue with Karnataka forest chief
news.para: The delegation met him at the Forest Bhavan in Bengaluru to address the agricultural community's challenges and the uncertainty stemming from forest department interventions.

news.title: Gram chaupals playing key role in selecting PMAY beneficiaries in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: Conducted on the principle of ‘Problem of the Village – Solution in the Village,' where personal and public grievances of villagers are addressed directly within their communities, the Gram Chaupals are organised every Friday in two Gram Panchayats of each development block.

news.title: Sambhal: Over 110 plots near Sambhal stepwell sold using fake will
news.para: They added that the area was originally part of the Laxmanganj locality, but as the town developed, a new colony named ‘Mughalpura' emerged.

news.title: Godrej Properties launches its first project in Hyderabad
news.para: Situated on about three acres of land with an estimated booking value of approximately Rs 1,300 crore, Godrej Madison Avenue will feature 1.2 million sq ft of saleable area.

news.title: Kolkata metro plans to extend Joka-Esplanade purple line to Eden Gardens
news.para: This is good news not only for cricket and football lovers but also scores of people who commute daily to workplaces around Strand Road, Babughat, Calcutta High Court and BBD Bag.

news.title: Gujarat's law struggles to curb illegal constructions in Ahmedabad
news.para: The law, which was first introduced in early 2000s, then in 2011 and finally enacted again in 2022, has been unable to stop new illegal constructions or additions to existing residential or commercial buildings.

news.title: DTCP issues notices for building code violations in Gurugram’s DLF areas
news.para: The department said it has already issued 1,138 notices to property owners in DLF-3, and more notices will be sent.

news.title: Gujarat HC exempts GST on leasehold rights for industrial plots, to boost investment
news.para: The ruling is poised to support smoother transactions and potentially boost investment in the industrial and commercial leasing market across India.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body seals 830 commercial properties
news.para: According to BBMP’s Special Commissioner (Revenue) Munish Moudgil, the BBMP has sealed properties across its eight zones as part of its action against tax defaulters.

news.title: No construction here: Warning boards soon on New Noida land
news.para: ​During a meeting on Thursday, CEO Lokesh M, along with Bulandshahr district magistrate CP Singh and officials from the Noida and Bulandshahr development authorities, asked for the installation of boards that warned villagers of demolition of unauthorised structures.

news.title: Lucknow development body earns Rs 450 crore in e-auction
news.para: The auction, held on Jan 7, followed registration from Nov 11, 2024, to Jan 3, and saw 59 out of 325 properties sold.

news.title: Projects under Ludhiana smart city mission may miss more deadlines
news.para: ​Despite the long time they have already taken, projects, including the 24x7 surface water supply project for selected areas, bioremediation of legacy waste (first phase), and establishment of construction and demolition waste plants, are still pending.

news.title: Property allottees pay heavy price for Chandigarh estate office's glitch
news.para: The incorrect tagging of properties during the digitalisation of records has created substantial challenges, with owners spending years attempting to correct these errors.

news.title: NCLAT gives go-ahead for Indiabulls Real Estate-Embassy Group merger
news.para: ​"We set aside the impugned order of NCLT, Chandigarh and allow the prayer to sanction the scheme of amalgamation between the appellants (Indiabulls Real Estate, Embassy one & NAM Estates)," said a two-member NCLAT bench.

news.title: Regularisation plea can be entertained only if structure is irregular, not illegal: HC
news.para: The high court held that an application under the Regularisation Act can be entertained only if the structure is an irregular structure and not an illegal structure, and it was in existence and constructed as an irregular structure prior to Feb 28, 2014.

news.title: Signature Global acquires 16.12 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: Signature Global had reported pre-sales of Rs 86.7 billion during the first nine months of FY25, recording 178 per cent growth year-on-year.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to redevelop 10,300 sq meter land in Mumbai
news.para: The company expects to be entitled to a free sale component of around 3.2 lakh sq ft from the development and redevelopment of the said land.
